If you need a tool to deal with act 1 hallways and elites, this does the job admirably. It's a ton of frontloaded damage for 2 energy, and slime boss should be able to heal up most of the resulting tackle damage using their starting relic, and various other healing cards in their pool. However, that's simultaneously all it does, and it actually junks your deck up making it worse in long fights once you reshuffle. This has a terrible transition as you move between acts and get into more medium and long fights, and actively harms you in a way that's pretty difficult to mitigate unless you just choose not to cast it (similar to wild strike for ironclad, but that at least has some status synergies like evolve). I wonder if the tackle this generates ought to exhaust itself to make this less awkward? I feel like it making an extra tackle is supposed to support the theoretical "tackle deck" with recklessness, roll through, and the helmet shop relic. However, that deck just doesn't really exist as a viable option at higher ascensions, since it completely lacks utility options.

I think you would really like to do better than this as slime boss, and look for damage cards that transition better into the later stages of the game. That's not to say that it isn't functional as a card to carry you through act 1 (especially with the staggering +7 upgrade), and you can probably even afford to take a few less pure frontloaded cards when you take one this effective at the job. Ideally though, you're taking other cards that have more utility and that don't hurt your late game. Most of the other tackles are better than this, since they don't junk your deck up, and some have reasonable synergies with your card pool.
